parameters: Locked... I need a key to get through this.
<Huh, feels like there's something behind this bookshelf...>
<Alright, not my usual scene - but it’s the best
place to start if I'm gonna find out more about
demons and the deal I suppose.>
<And I think I just found my two
best study buddies on the subject.>
My brothers and sisters, thank you for coming today. Another
beautiful Sunday morning. Yes it is days such as this that I
truly feel blessed with all that The Lord has given me...
<Hey, that must Oluchi and Chiwa’s dad.
Dude looks pretty ripped to be a pastor.>
I have my health, I have two miracles that
I’m proud to say are my children...
... I have a beautiful wife, whom is currently on her own
mission, and I pray for her quick return... She has been
I’d love to see her too.>
But I am also filled with much anger and sadness,
as a unholy deceiver is in our midst!
An intruder on our very way of life!
Yes, The Devil takes many forms, and his arsenal grows by
the day. We all see it, and most ignore it. Temptation is
in a bottle, on our television screens, even in our schools.
But looking at all of you, old faces and new, I am reminded
that we are never alone. Our community will persevere
during these trying times as we have before.
And speaking of new faces, I’d like all of you to give your
most heartfelt welcome to our newest member, Sister Grace.
<Damn! That’s certainly another good reason to start
coming to church. I’m sure I could squeeze in some time,
and other things, while I’m here.>
Thank ye, Father. Ah don’t know how long Ah’ll be in your
lovelay community, but ah go where The Lord asks of mae.
Me time may be brief, but ah’ll sure an truly put the fear
of The Almighty in sinners, as me life’s mission dictates.
For our beloved Father is right, evil is ever present
among the flock, an Ah know what must be done.
... Thank ye all fer your welcome.
Sister Grace will indeed be a wonderful
addition to our town, however long it may be.
<Holy crap, I thought that would never end. What a complete
waste of time! I don’t have any useful information or fresh
ideas that can help me, just a hour and a half guilt trip.>
<Oh well, at least I can now go talk to Oluchi and Chiwa.>
Hey there, ladies. Fine Sunday today, isn’t it?
See, Chiwa? Told you he would show.
Really? Right in front of him?
*Sigh* I’m sorry, \N[001].  I don’t want you to feel
unwelcome here. In fact WE’RE genuinely happy to see you.
You don’t know many guys who would spend their
weekend at church rather than sleeping in?
Frankly, we don’t know many guys in general to be honest.
So like a parent? Got it.
Ah, cmon. He can’t be that bad-
Good afternoon, my angels. Who’s our new friend here?
This is \N[001]. He’s from our school.
And he asked us about spiritual questions at school.
Even came today when we offered!
Tell me, what do you know about the Good Book?
Honestly, not much. I haven’t read the bible,
was kind of waiting for the movie.
Ha! A humorous young man too...
But I do not joke about The Lord.
W-What I meant to say is that I’m admittedly ignorant to
the spiritual life, and I want to know more.
The truth is, sir, is that I’m kind of in a... Dark place
right now. I’m running out of options, and I’m afraid for
Your daughters have been very kind to me, and I
wanted to get to know the church, and them, better.
That is, if you’ll have me.
My son, you truly are unique. Forgive me,
it is uncommon for me to see a young man
of your age show interest in The Almighty.
Usually boys of your age show their maturity in other,
more undesirable and perverse ways. As a father to two
wonderful young women, I’m sure you can understand.
\N[001] is a good guy, honest. He’s been nothing but polite.
So... Could Chiwa and I maybe go do something fun with
\N[001] this afternoon? Because I was thinking the three
of us could go to the mall and-
But girls, what about the bake sale?
Yes, and the proceeds go towards various
activities, like our upcoming nature hike.
Oluchi and I have to run the table, but we could
Yeah, and we’ll likely run into each other at school too!
<Damn. I need to think of an excuse to stick around, and
maybe something that can let Oluchi and Chiwa take off for
What if I sweep up a little? Dust some corners?
I don’t have much going on today.
<Well, I could be doing literally anything else for my free
time, but I’m not telling Father Freeman that!>
Son, you continue to impress me. I’d be delighted to have
you spruce up the church. I’m sure we have generations of
The girls should be able to point you in the right places
should you have any questions. But don’t mingle too long,
they’ll be busy handing out sweets.
Come find us if you need anything.
You’re a fine young man, son. Do not disappoint me.
Wouldn’t dream of it, Mr... Pastor... Father Freeman!
Splendid! And please, call me Markus.
Sister Grace! Have you met our new convert, \N[001], yet?
... Ah don’t believe Ah’ve had the pleasure.
<Oh but I think you will, very soon if I can help it.>
Father, I believe a woman is waitin’ fer you in the
The work never ends, does it? \N[001], I’m sure Sister
Grace can assist you from here. Thank you again.
So I guess I’ll just be going now, maybe hit
up the bakery table for a cookie or-
What are ye, you mingin’ brat?
Don’t go playin’ daft with mae, munter!
Ah can feel the dark magic surroundin’ you!
Look, I’m not exactly sure what you’re talking about but-
You're no demon cause o' where we’re standin’, but sometin’
is off with you. Demon mixed with... Heavenly blessin’?
What kind of deals have you been makin’, you little-
Alright you know what? The hell with this.
So you made a bargain with HER?
YOU WILL TELL ME WHERE THAT SLEEKIT PIT WENCH IS!
<Well fuck, that’s clearly not a good sign! Who the hell
is this lady?! Why didn’t my powers work?
<Holy shit! She just fucking materialized a sword - what
the fuck have I gotten myself in to?!>
Back off or... I’m warning you! I-I’ll...
Don’t make mae sully the house of God with yer blood now.
Just tell mae where the beast be.
Aha! See? Back! Fire bad! Back, you fiend!
Ah ain’t a blasted zombie you daft-!
Jumping Jerusalem! What is going on in here?!
Everyone is okay at our table, but all
the pastries are ruined. What happened?
A-Ah just got ‘ere meself! Was hopin’ the
hooligan ‘ere might explain a thing or two.
It was an accident, I swear! I... I was trying to get one
of the corners by the ceiling, I leaned too close to
I think I know EXACTLY what happened...
You were really trying to go above and beyond to help,
and in your desire to do so, you got careless.
Yes, sir. That's right. I’m really sorry Mr. Freeman.
I won’t lie, this isn’t exactly your best first day.
HOWEVER, I can really tell by your character and honesty
We all make mistakes, and in truth, this
might have been a blessing in disguise.
Really? I mean, I sort of ruined the charity bake sale,
and there’s probably some water damage in here.
You exposed something I’ve been putting off for some time,
son, and that’s the fire hazard of all these lit candles.
While the atmosphere is great, I shouldn’t have put
that in front of my flock’s safety.
So I suppose I should be thankful.
The Lord certainly works in mysterious ways.
Well, the bake sale is a bust. Daddy, is there anything
you’d like us to do to help clean up?
Yeah, I doubt anyone wants soggy banana bread.
It’s fine, girls. I’ll have to call some people, insurance
mostly, and we’ll figure out another fundraiser later.
Why don’t you two head home, and then we’ll have our family
pizza night like always to forget about today’s excitement.
Enjoy the fresh air, I’ll be home later. Oh, and \N[001]?
We’ll see you at the next service.
Sister Grace, would you mind getting a mop?
I have a few calls to make.
